  "text": "With robustness and efficiency in perspective, the Deep Projection CNN (DPN) method in [CITATION_1] employs what the authors call model adaptation to exploit the repetitive structures in the LR image. The DPN has three parts: feature extraction/representation via stacked CNN/ReLU layers, inference via CNN/ReLU based projections, and CNN only HR reconstruction. The authors claim up to 0.3dB PSNR gain with a 40-layer DPN (and 0.7M parameters) over reference methods, like A+, SRCNN and VDSR (same 20 layers and 0.7M parameters, as in [CITATION_2] ). The reported results are almost the same as reported [CITATION_3] and the latter, despite being from the same first author, does not appear on the reference list. In addition, no time efficiency results are reported.",
